                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="394111" author="adilger" created="Fri, 24 Nov 2023 06:58:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem here is because conf-sanity test_28a on b2_10 is using parameter &quot;&lt;tt&gt;obdfilter.&amp;#42;.writethrough_cache_enable&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; but this moved to &quot;&lt;tt&gt;osd-ldiskfs.&amp;#42;.writethrough_cache_enable&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and removed from conf-sanity in commit v2_11_54_0-77-g115bba9ffbe6.  This is another case where testing with the old conf-sanity.sh from b2_10 should skip this subtest. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="259246" author="mdiep" created="Thu, 5 Dec 2019 21:37:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test_28a() { # &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4221&quot; title=&quot;lctl conf_param &amp;lt;obdname&amp;gt;.ost.writethrough_cache_enable=N does not work anymore&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4221&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4221&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        [[ $(lustre_version_code ost1) -ge $(version_code 2.5.52) ]] ||&lt;br/&gt;
                skip &quot;Need OST version at least 2.5.52&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
        [ &quot;$(facet_fstype ost1)&quot; = &quot;zfs&quot; ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;br/&gt;
                skip &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4221&quot; title=&quot;lctl conf_param &amp;lt;obdname&amp;gt;.ost.writethrough_cache_enable=N does not work anymore&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4221&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4221&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: no such proc params for ZFS OSTs&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see we skip on zfs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="246369" author="jamesanunez" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2019 18:58:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good question. This is for ldiskfs testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="246368" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2019 18:56:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this ZFS ? For ZFS writethrough_cache_enable doesn&apos;t exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
